<TITLE> Former soldier gets life </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barguna, Apr 29 (bdnews24.com) A Barguna court on Thursday sentenced a former army soldier to life imprisonment for the murder of his sister-in-law. Shahidul Islam, 50, was also fined Tk 1 lakh by Barguna's women and children repression tribunal judge Kazi Golam Sarwar. Islam will have to serve a further one year upon failure to pay the fine. Case details reveal that Islam had a romantic relation with his sister-in-law Lavli, 22, of Shaeber Howla village. On Nov 5, 2003 Islam took Lavli and her friend Narzia Begum on a day trip to Kuakata. Narzia and Islam got involved on the trip and Islam killed his sister-in-law on the journey back the next day near their village. Mokhlesur Rahman, a member of the local village police, filed a case with Barguna Sadr police the next day. Narzia and Islam were arrested from Jailkhana village of the upazila two days later and the charge sheet was submitted on Aug 31, 2004. The court set Narzia free. Public prosecutor Bhuban Chandra Hawladar conducted the case for the state. However, there was no lawyer for the accused. bd
